what is peer cli??

The Peer CLI is Fabric‚Äôs primary command-line interface tool used to interact with peer nodes in your network. It's provided through the Fabric peer binary, which you run directly in your terminal (typically inside the CLI Docker container or on your local host if Fabric binaries are installed).

üõ†Ô∏è What It Is
A client executable named peer ‚Äî located in the Fabric bin/ directory.

Used for many key operations:

Channel management: create/join/fetch/update channels

Chaincode lifecycle: install, package, approve, commit, query, invoke

Peer administration: check node status, manage logs, etc. 
