üß≠ Organizing the peer CLI
Here's the general command structure:

php-template
Copy
Edit
peer <subcommand> <action> [flags]
Examples:

peer channel create -o orderer.example.com:7050 ‚Ä¶

peer chaincode install -n mycc -v 1.0 -p path/to/cc

peer node status ‚Äî shows the running peer node state 
